# .pii-allow — regexes that suppress scripts/check-pii.sh hits on
# specific lines. One extended regex per line; blank lines and lines
# starting with '#' are ignored.
#
# The regex matches the offending line's content (not the file path).
# Adding a pattern here lets a matching line through the scan.
#
# Example (uncomment to allow CI-docs examples that mention
# /Users/runner/ as a canonical CI home path):
#
#   /Users/runner/

# Canonical CI home paths — appear in scripts/check_pii.sh's own
# documentation as examples of what the scan catches.
/Users/runner/
/home/runner/
